options.description: An existing enrollment token for securely joining a cluster
Creates a pid file in the specified path on start
Turns off standard output/error streams logging in console
Prints Elasticsearch version information and exits

subcommands.name: elasticsearch start
subcommands.raw_help_text:
Starts Elasticsearch

Option                Description                                               
------                -----------                                               
-E <KeyValuePair>     Configure a setting                                       
-V, --version         Prints Elasticsearch version information and exits        
-d, --daemonize       Starts Elasticsearch in the background                    
--enrollment-token    An existing enrollment token for securely joining a       
                        cluster                                                 
-h, --help            Show help                                                 
-p, --pidfile <Path>  Creates a pid file in the specified path on start         
-q, --quiet           Turns off standard output/error streams logging in console
-s, --silent          Show minimal output                                       
-v, --verbose         Show verbose output
